================================================================================

Exercise 1: Create Your First Repository
  1. Create a folder called "practice-git"
  2. Initialize Git in that folder
  3. Create a file called "notes.txt"
  4. Add and commit the file

Exercise 2: Make Changes & Track Them
  1. Edit "notes.txt" and add some content
  2. Use git diff to see what changed
  3. Commit the change with a meaningful message
  4. View the log to see your history

Exercise 3: Create & Merge Branches
  1. Create a branch called "feature/new-feature"
  2. Make changes in that branch and commit
  3. Switch back to main
  4. Merge the feature branch
  5. Delete the feature branch

Exercise 4: Practice Undo
  1. Make some changes to a file
  2. Realize you made a mistake
  3. Use git restore to undo the changes
  4. Verify the file is back to normal

